relation: Darrow1 - #23 Preparing for the worst, Ness and Paula figure out their next goal. However, nothing can prepare them for what comes next.
Darrow1 - #24 While children may sometimes make decent projectile weapons, it is advisable only to throw the children of other people and not your own. Unless they're really annoying, I suppose.

Darrow1 - #25 Entering the graveyard only leads to bigger frights, but nothing is scarier than an enraged Paula. Unfortunately for Ness, this means being delegated to the "damsel in distress" while Paula gets the "hardened action hero" spot.
Darrow1 - #26 A brief attempt at progressing through Threed ends in failure. ZOMBIE FAILURE.

Darrow1 - #27 Ness discovers the true female form for the first time and also finds himself smack in the middle of the latest installment of Dateline's To Catch a Predator. The guy in the hat? Totally Chris Hansen.
